  "body": "<!-- Thanks so much for your PR, your contribution is appreciated! ❤️ -->\r\n\r\n- [x] I have followed (at least) the [PR section of the contributing guide](https://github.com/mui/material-ui/blob/HEAD/CONTRIBUTING.md#sending-a-pull-request).\r\n\r\nAddresses https://github.com/mui/material-ui/pull/36773#discussion_r1158081495 and https://github.com/mui/material-ui/pull/36400#discussion_r1162807990. \r\n\r\nThe script strictly checked for returnValue and parameters to be of the `interface` type. I'm not sure why it was added like that. Is there any particular reason? We should allow both type aliases and interfaces. \r\n",
